taxon.name: Marpesia petreus

default_photo.attribution: (c) djhiker, some rights reserved (CC BY-NC), uploaded by djhiker

taxon.wikipedia_summary: Marpesia petreus, the ruddy daggerwing, is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family. It is found in Brazil north through Central America, Mexico, and the West Indies to southern Florida. Strays are found as far north as Arizona, Colorado, Nebraska, Kansas, and southern Texas.
